metadata.description: Strokes are a fundamental aspect of art, and they can be used in a variety of ways to create different effects. In painting, for example, strokes can be used to create texture, to convey movement, or to suggest emotion. They can be thick or thin, short or long, rough or smooth, and they can be made with a variety of tools, including brushes, palette knives, and even fingers. This is a generative Art Experiment // All Images are processed and designed to be unique and represent a different style and interpretation // 277 NFTs max // Less dots = more Rare.
